Peter Hepplewhite is a British [[author]]. He is most well known for his Horrible Histories title The Awesome Egyptians which he co-authored with [[Terry Deary]].<ref>[https://www.amazon.co.uk/Awesome-Egyptians-Horrible-Histories/dp/0439944031/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1398726457&sr=1-1&keywords=The+awesome+Egyptians The Awesome Egyptians Amazon page]</ref> However he has written many other children's [[history]] books,<ref>[https://www.amazon.co.uk/Peter-Hepplewhite/e/B001ITVRFE Peter Hepplewhite's Amazon author page]</ref><ref>[http://www.goodreads.com/author/list/262492.Peter_Hepplewhite Peter Hepplwhite's Goodreads page]</ref> often co-writing with his longtime writing partner [[Neil Tonge]].

Peter was born in [[Hartlepool]] in June 1954 and lived there until his teens. For the last 16 years he has lived in [[North Tyneside]], and until recently he worked as the Education Officer at the Tyne & Wear Archives.<ref>https://www.hachettechildrens.co.uk/books/detail.page?isbn=9780750288224</ref>

